Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry produce.

Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @garlic powder{1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Place on prepared baking sheet. Evenly spread a thin layer of @sour cream{2%tbsp} onto tops of chicken (you may have some left over). Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast on middle rack until crust is golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve @pasta cooking water{1 1/2%cups}, then drain. (Keep empty #pot{} handy for next step.)

Meanwhile, heat a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Transfer bacon to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, chop into small pieces.

Let pan with bacon fat cool slightly, then carefully add @spinach{5%ounce}. (TIP: Allowing the pan to cool will help prevent splattering.) Cook over medium heat, stirring, until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Once pasta and bacon are done, return empty #pot{} used for pasta to medium heat. Add @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, remaining garlic powder, and @reserved pasta cooking water{1%cup}; whisk to combine. Cook, whisking, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Lower heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{2%tbsp} until melted and combined.

Add drained spaghetti, @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, half the chives, and @butter{2%tbsp} to pot with alfredo sauce. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Stir in bacon and spinach. (TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.) Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide pasta between plates. Top with crispy chicken. Garnish with remaining chives and serve.